  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Intermediate Care Service - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_intermediate_care_service">Intermediate Care Service</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service">SERVICE</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_intermediate_care_service">Intermediate Care Service</xref>
 provides support for a short time to help 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 recover and increase their independence.  </p>
  <p>
There are four types of 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_intermediate_care_service">Intermediate Care Service</xref>
:  </p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_reablement_intermediate_care_service">Reablement Intermediate Care Service</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_crisis_response_intermediate_care_service">Crisis Response Intermediate Care Service</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_home-based_intermediate_care_service">Home-based Intermediate Care Service</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_community_bed-based_intermediate_care_service">Community Bed-based Intermediate Care Service</xref>
            <p>.</p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>

